invalid type: string "Context:\nSuppose you have an array of size N. We can work backwards to compute how many elements we copied at each capacity increase. When we increase the array to K elements, the array was previously half that size. Therefore, we needed to copy K/2 elements. The total number of copies to insert N elements is roughly N/2 + N/4 + N/8 + ... + 2 + 1, which is just less than N.˙